        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued July 23 at 6:37PM MDT by NWS Cheyenne WY</headline>
        <description>At 637 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Montrose, or 23 miles south of Edgemont, moving east at 25 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and nickel size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Montrose and Toadstool Geological Park and Campground.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.</instruction>
